description: Informational repository for the Pacific Islands Fisheries Science Center (NOAA, NMFS)

The Data Validation Module (DVM) was developed to provide a framework to validate data entered in the database based on flexible data validation criteria that can be developed and implemented in Oracle Views by a data manager/developer without requiring application development skills.  A series of QC Views can be developed to identify problematic values in the database and implemented in the framework to allow each criteria to be evaluated on the given data stream.

The Database Version Control Module (VCM) was developed to provide a safe and easy way to install and upgrade database modules deployed on a given Oracle database instance.  The VCM provides information on which database module versions were installed and when they were installed on a database instance.  This module is used to apply the necessary database upgrades in the correct order to upgrade a given database module to a desired version.
The Database Logging Module (DLM) was developed to provide a method to log entries in an Oracle database for any modules that utilize an Oracle database.
This project was created to provide a GitHub repository template that fulfills all feasible NOAA GitHub requirements

Centralized Cruise Database to track information about each PIFSC research cruise including activities, chief scientists, regions, etc. to remove the need for each division/program to manage this information
This project was developed to provide a database module to define configuration options that can be used by any Oracle database modules

This project was developed to maintain an inventory of software and data resources to promote reuse of the tools, SOPs, etc. that can be utilized the improve, streamline, and support the data processes within PIFSC
Information for students working with PIFSC and their mentors
Fork for capturing query metrics for the IBBS data system
Custom implementation of the web application metrics project for the International Billfish Biosampling System (IBBS) web app
Project to capture SQLPlus query performance metrics for defined queries in a given database
Fork for capturing SQLPlus query performance metrics for the PARR Tools data system
Project to capture web application performance metrics from the end-user perspective
Custom implementation of the web application performance metrics project for the PARR Tools web app
Mock-up website for centralized resources using minimal-mistakes Jekyll theme
